-- BMW sees China sales up 25-30 pct this year - CFO
-- 
-- Wed May 23, 2012 10:17pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/05/24/us-bmw-china-idUSBRE84N02T20120524

 

 BEIJING  (Reuters) - BMW Group ( BMWG.DE ) expects its China sales to rise 25-30 percent this year, Chief Financial Officer Friedrich Eichiner told reporters in Beijing on Thursday. 
 BMW Group sold about 1.6 million cars worldwide in 2011. It sold about 426,000, another record, in the first quarter of this year. (Reporting by Li Ran and Don Durfee; Editing by  Paul Tait )